            "icon_width": 24,
            "title": "Saftely reminder For Yozma Riders",
            "content": "<p>To ensure a safe and responsible riding experience, please review these key guidelines before use:</p><ul><li><strong>Wear proper protective gear</strong>, including a helmet, elbow pads, and knee pads.</li><li><strong>Check essential components</strong> before each ride: brakes, tires, handlebar stability, and battery security/charge level.</li><li><strong>Select an appropriate speed mode</strong> based on the rider’s experience. Young riders and beginners should start with low-speed mode and follow all local regulations.</li><li><strong>Use the original charger only</strong>; avoid third-party charging devices. Unplug after charging or when not in use.</li><li><strong>No unauthorized modifications</strong>, as alterations may lead to safety risks or improper operation.</li></ul>",
